The polished floor featured dozens of booths with colorful banners from various companies, including a robotics startup flying a small drone, a cybersecurity company running a password cracking challenge on a laptop, and a data science company displaying a live dashboard of fair attendance metrics. Career counselors advised attendees to maintain eye contact, particularly at the resume review table near the stage, and redirected unsure students towards applicable industries, also guiding international students on visa sponsorship requirements. Workshops on networking etiquette occurred in an adjoining classroom, while alumni panels, nonprofit representatives, and interview sign-up sheets contributed to the ongoing activities. A welcome announcement outlined the fair schedule over the PA system, and students utilized tablets at kiosks to upload resumes to the fair database.
